<p>October to May is the best time to visit Andaman. This period is perfect for the tourists to explore island and enjoy a trip without any issues. </p>

<h2>How to reach Andaman</h2>

<p><strong>By Air</strong>- Flights are the fastest way to reach Andaman. You can get direct flights to Veer Savarkar International Airport, Port Blair, from your nearest airport. </p>

<p><strong>By Train &amp; Ferry</strong>- The most budget friendly way to visit Andaman, but time-consuming at the same time. You can take a train from your hometown to the coastal areas like Kolkata, Visakhapatnam, or Chennai, and then board a ferry to Port Blair. </p>

<h2>Best Places to visit in Andaman / Top Tourist Places in Andaman</h2>

<h3>Port Blair in Andaman</h3>
<p>The capital city of Andaman is Nicobar Island, an Indian territory in the Bay of Bengal. This beautiful place acts as the entry point of the Andaman trip for many visitors. Explore the rich history and British penal colony with invisit&rsquo;s Andaman tour packages. </p>

<h3>Havelock Island in Andaman</h3>
<p>Swaraj Dweep or popularly known as Havelock&rsquo;s Island, is one of the best places to visit in Andaman. The place is well-known for its stunning scenic beauty and vibrant coral reefs. Explore the tropical paradise, which holds many popular beaches like Radhanagar Beach or Elephant Beach. </p>

<h3>Baratang Island in Andaman</h3>
<p>Baratang Isaland is nothing but a hidden gem in Andaman that offers unique and off-beat experiences to its visitors. Explore the limestone cave, mud volcano, and dense mangrove forest with invisit&rsquo;s Andaman travel packages. </p>

<h3>Neil Island in Andaman</h3>
<p>Shaheed Dweep, or Neil Island, is a tiny but beautiful island located south of Port Blair. Popular for its laid-back atmosphere, beaches, and colourful coral reefs, Neil Island is one of the best places to visit in Andaman. </p>

<h3>Ross and Smith Islands in Andaman</h3>
<p>The twin island of North Andaman is popular for its beautiful beaches and scenic surroundings. These two are separate islands but connected by a white sand bridge that looks phenomenal.  Book Andaman tour packages to explore the best places to visit in Andaman. </p>

<h3>Diglipur, in Andaman</h3>
<p>Diglipur, the largest town in the northern Andaman Islands, is known for its adventure activities and off-beat track experiences. Book Andaman holiday packages to explore the beauty of Diglipur in Andaman. </p>

<h3>Mayabunder in Andaman</h3>
<p>The alluring beauty of Andaman, Mayabunder, is one of the best places to visit in Andaman. Explore the off-beat places and hop on to the serene beaches with Andaman tour packages. </p>

<h3>Rangat in Andaman</h3>
<p>A vibrant town, located in the middle of Andaman Island, is one of the best places to visit in Andaman. It offers a glimpse into the natural beauty of the island with our Andaman travel packages. </p>

<h3>Nicobar Island in Andaman</h3>
