  <h2>Best Places for Honeymoon in Andaman</h2>


<h3>Jolly Buoy Island in Andaman</h3>
<p>The natural beauty that surrounds this island will undoubtedly captivate you and your spouse. Jolly Bouy Island is part of the Mahatma Gandhi National Marine Park. As a result, you may try diving and discover aquatic life here. If you visit the island during the winter, you can even opt to relax in the sun.</p>

<h3>Elephant Beach in Andaman</h3>
<p>The beach is well-known for its coral reefs and colourful marine life, which is why it is often included in Andaman vacation packages. You may go snorkelling or scuba diving here. This is a one-of-a-kind beach that you must visit to boost your romance on your honeymoon.</p>


<h3>Laxmanpur Beach in Andaman</h3>
<p>Laxmanpur Beach is a lovely beach with clear water. The magnificent sunset and gentle air on your face are an unforgettable experience that you can only have here. Newlyweds who wish to be surrounded by nature should visit this beach, and they may even include it in their Andaman vacation packages.</p>


<h3>Amkunj Beach in Andaman</h3>
<p>Amkunj Beach is a great area for isolation, with a clean sea and gentle waves. You will not have much to do here, but you may spend your time getting to know your companion better and talking about whatever you like. </p>

